		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: LoveUI... has button, Textfield, tableView]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=8225#p8225"><![CDATA[
Hmm... that's a problem. Here's a short term get around, but you'll likely remove key-repeats too. <div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>aContext.keyRepeatSpeed=3000</code></pre></div>The default value is 300 ms. Try raise it to 3 seconds and keys shouldn't repeat like you described (It'll only repeat after holding the key for 3 seconds, slowly accelerating from that base amount.). <br><br>I'm suspecting this could be a timer and input problem. Maybe also to do with zeroes. This will definitely be fixed when 0.6.0 comes out, because that version comes with key repeats, so I don't need to implement my own anymore.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=85">appleide</a> — Tue Jul 14, 2009 10:16 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
